THE Community Police Forum (CPF)/Gemeenskapspolisieforum (GPF) in Oudtshoorn is a group of interested individuals as well as people from different member organisations in the community and police representatives who meet and discuss safety problems in their communities. If you are interested in becoming a member of the CPF you can contact WO Leilah Claassen at the police station at 044 203 9005. • As u belangstel om ’n lid van die GPF te word, kan u ao Leilah Claassen kontak op die grondvloer by die polisiekantoor in Baron van Reedestraat en ’n vorm invul.